1
00:00:00,390 --> 00:00:03,970
Hypertext Markup Language, or HTML, is a language

2
00:00:03,970 --> 00:00:06,550
that defines the structure of content on a

3
00:00:06,450 --> 00:00:06,950
web page.

4
00:00:07,029 --> 00:00:10,370
Development started in 1989 at SERN by Tim

5
00:00:10,370 --> 00:00:12,370
Berners-Lee, who had just invented the world's

6
00:00:12,370 --> 00:00:14,850
first web browser, World Wide Web, the origin

7
00:00:14,850 --> 00:00:15,930
of www.

8
00:00:16,570 --> 00:00:18,710
But he needed a publishing language to display

9
00:00:18,710 --> 00:00:20,770
content within it, so he chose a syntax

10
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:23,890
based on the standard generalized markup language, which

11
00:00:23,890 --> 00:00:26,410
uses opening and closing tags to provide meaning

12
00:00:26,410 --> 00:00:29,510
to otherwise unorganized text, like h for heading,

13
00:00:29,810 --> 00:00:32,550
p for paragraph, and most importantly, a for

14
00:00:32,550 --> 00:00:34,670
anchor to link to a different web page.

15
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:37,070
The language underwent many changes during the initial

16
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:39,170
rise of the internet and was standardized as

17
00:00:39,170 --> 00:00:42,110
HTML5 in 2008, the version we know and

18
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:42,670
love today.

19
00:00:42,930 --> 00:00:45,710
Modern HTML contains tags to handle a variety

20
00:00:45,710 --> 00:00:48,710
of different media types, like video, audio, and

21
00:00:48,710 --> 00:00:51,050
canvas to draw custom graphics on the fly.

22
00:00:51,170 --> 00:00:53,690
The typical HTML element starts with an opening

23
00:00:53,690 --> 00:00:54,910
and closing tag.

24
00:00:55,090 --> 00:00:57,010
In the middle, we have content, which might

25
00:00:57,010 --> 00:00:59,990
be text, or additional HTML elements called children.

26
00:01:00,310 --> 00:01:02,370
The opening tag may also have one or

27
00:01:02,370 --> 00:01:04,810
more attributes, which are key value pairs that

28
00:01:04,810 --> 00:01:07,190
can customize the appearance or behavior of the

29
00:01:07,190 --> 00:01:07,490
element.

30
00:01:07,690 --> 00:01:09,410
To build your first web page, create a

31
00:01:09,410 --> 00:01:12,750
file named index.html. This file contains a

32
00:01:12,750 --> 00:01:15,130
hierarchy of nodes based on the document object

33
00:01:15,130 --> 00:01:16,250
model, or DOM.

34
00:01:16,530 --> 00:01:18,710
A web page starts with an HTML tag

35
00:01:18,710 --> 00:01:21,510
and has exactly two children, a head and

36
00:01:21,510 --> 00:01:21,930
a body.

37
00:01:22,150 --> 00:01:24,610
The head contains things that aren't directly shown

38
00:01:24,610 --> 00:01:26,750
in the web page, like a title or

39
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:28,570
a meta tag, to give the page a

40
00:01:28,570 --> 00:01:28,950
description.

41
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:31,250
But notice how the meta element has no

42
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:32,030
closing tag.

43
00:01:32,270 --> 00:01:34,510
Closing tags are generally optional when an element

44
00:01:34,510 --> 00:01:35,830
is fully self-contained.

45
00:01:36,010 --> 00:01:38,310
The body contains the actual UI for the

46
00:01:38,310 --> 00:01:38,850
end user.

47
00:01:39,010 --> 00:01:40,890
We might start with an h1 heading, followed

48
00:01:40,890 --> 00:01:42,310
by a paragraph of content.

49
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:44,270
To add an image, we use an image

50
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:46,370
tag, which you'll notice is self-closing.

51
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:48,970
Then define the source attribute as the file

52
00:01:48,970 --> 00:01:50,490
path to the image, and you'll want to

53
00:01:50,490 --> 00:01:51,930
give it an old description to make it

54
00:01:51,930 --> 00:01:53,930
accessible to robots and screen readers.

55
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:56,290
What makes web pages revolutionary, though, is their

56
00:01:56,290 --> 00:01:58,370
ability to link to other web pages on

57
00:01:58,370 --> 00:01:59,810
the information superhighway.

58
00:01:59,970 --> 00:02:01,650
Use an anchor tag to create a link,

59
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:03,970
then define the href attribute as the web

60
00:02:03,970 --> 00:02:05,750
page that you want to navigate to when

61
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:06,110
clicked.

62
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:09,490
HTML also provides structural tags like division or

63
00:02:09,490 --> 00:02:11,770
div, which are often used to group elements

64
00:02:11,770 --> 00:02:13,850
together, where they can be styled to represent

65
00:02:13,850 --> 00:02:15,990
complex UI elements like navbars.

66
00:02:16,230 --> 00:02:17,690
When you're happy with your code, grab the

67
00:02:17,690 --> 00:02:19,890
full file path to the HTML file and

68
00:02:19,890 --> 00:02:21,470
paste it into any web browser.

69
00:02:21,770 --> 00:02:24,110
Congratulations, you just built your first website!

70
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:26,810
This has been Hypertext Markup Language in 100

71
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:27,330
seconds.

72
00:02:27,470 --> 00:02:29,030
Hit the subscribe button so you don't miss

73
00:02:29,030 --> 00:02:30,110
the upcoming sequels.

74
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:32,050
Thanks for watching, and I will see you

75
00:02:32,050 --> 00:02:32,730
in the next one.
